    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - DISASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the hub of the front auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13027d5">Figure 135</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13027d5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027d5" filename="../figg13/G13027d5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 135. Remove Snap Ring From Hub of Front Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the rear face of the retainer ring as a base and press the drive gear through the
                bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13027d6">Figure 136</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13027d6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027d6" filename="../figg13/G13027d6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 136. Press Drive Gear Through Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the O-rings from the hub O.D. of the front auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13027d7">Figure 137</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13027d7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027d7" filename="../figg13/G13027d7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 137. Remove O-Rings From Hub O.D. of Front Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
